{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01MfUmVmV92rrXVQoft34dCw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# TaskFlow\n2\t\n3\tA full-stack task management application built with Express, React, and PostgreSQL.\n4\t\n5\t## Tech Stack\n6\t\n7\t- **Backend:** Node.js with Express\n8\t- **Frontend:** React (Vite)\n9\t- **Database:** PostgreSQL\n10\t- **Session Store:** Redis\n11\t- **Auth:** JWT-based authentication with bcrypt password hashing\n12\t\n13\t## Project Structure\n14\t\n15\t```\n16\tpackages/\n17\t  api/     Express REST API\n18\t  web/     React single-page application\n19\t```\n20\t\n21\t## Getting Started\n22\t\n23\t### Prerequisites\n24\t\n25\t- Docker and Docker Compose\n26\t- Node.js 20+\n27\t\n28\t### Running Locally\n29\t\n30\t1. Copy the example environment file:\n31\t   ```bash\n32\t   cp .env.example .env\n33\t   ```\n34\t\n35\t2. Start all services with Docker Compose:\n36\t   ```bash\n37\t   docker-compose up\n38\t   ```\n39\t\n40\t   This starts the API server on port 3001, the web dev server on port 5173, PostgreSQL on port 5432, and Redis on port 6379.\n41\t\n42\t3. For local development without Docker:\n43\t   ```bash\n44\t   npm install\n45\t   npm run dev\n46\t   ```\n47\t\n48\t### Environment Variables\n49\t\n50\t| Variable       | Description                  | Default                              |\n51\t|----------------|------------------------------|--------------------------------------|\n52\t| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string | `postgres://taskflow:taskflow@localhost:5432/taskflow` |\n53\t| `REDIS_URL`    | Redis connection string      | `redis://localhost:6379`             |\n54\t| `JWT_SECRET`   | Secret key for signing JWTs  | (required, no default)               |\n55\t| `PORT`         | API server port              | `3001`                               |\n56\t\n57\t## Testing\n58\t\n59\t```bash\n60\tnpm test\n61\t```\n62\t\n63\tRuns Jest test suites for the API package.\n64\t\n65\t## License\n66\t\n67\tMIT\n68\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dbab0d9f-faa5-4968-89c8-f0b289f0ffd3","uuid":"162a469f-ca9a-4470-9814-c936b290733c","timestamp":"2026-06-23T14:46:42.201Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/private/var/folders/38/_z2xr8rn0m33jpdp5jkbmd500000gn/T/agent-eval/2026-06-23-opus/cases/case-002-complex-node-webapp/README.md","content":"# TaskFlow\n\nA full-stack task management application built with Express, React, and PostgreSQL.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Backend:** Node.js with Express\n- **Frontend:** React (Vite)\n- **Database:** PostgreSQL\n- **Session Store:** Redis\n- **Auth:** JWT-based authentication with bcrypt password hashing\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\npackages/\n  api/     Express REST API\n  web/     React single-page application\n```\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Docker and Docker Compose\n- Node.js 20+\n\n### Running Locally\n\n1. Copy the example environment file:\n   ```bash\n   cp .env.example .env\n   ```\n\n2. Start all services with Docker Compose:\n   ```bash\n   docker-compose up\n   ```\n\n   This starts the API server on port 3001, the web dev server on port 5173, PostgreSQL on port 5432, and Redis on port 6379.\n\n3. For local development without Docker:\n   ```bash\n   npm install\n   npm run dev\n   ```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable       | Description                  | Default                              |\n|----------------|------------------------------|--------------------------------------|\n| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string | `postgres://taskflow:taskflow@localhost:5432/taskflow` |\n| `REDIS_URL`    | Redis connection string      | `redis://localhost:6379`             |\n| `JWT_SECRET`   | Secret key for signing JWTs  | (required, no default)               |\n| `PORT`         | API server port              | `3001`                               |\n\n## Testing\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\n\nRuns Jest test suites for the API package.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":68,"startLine":1,"totalLines":68}}}
